  "texts": [
    "We find that, by going through the candidate algebras listed in section 3.1 and solving the algebra conditions with the explicit Rep(D 8) F-symbols in (3.5), there are 12 different algebra objects which are listed in table 2; all of them are Morita inequivalent except for the pair A = 1, V ⊗ V in the Morita trivial class.",
